`conclusion.txt` is written with score **30** (leaning "No"). 

Key findings:
- Pearson r(masfem, deaths) = 0.117, p = 0.26 — not significant
- After controlling for storm severity, masfem coef = 0.021, p = 0.54 — also not significant
- Spearman rho ≈ 0.002, p = 0.99 — essentially zero rank correlation
- Female-named hurricanes had higher mean deaths (58 vs 14), but this likely reflects confounding (e.g., older storms had female names and less warning infrastructure), not name-gender perception effects
